ref: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.128, p.297 (2017)
title: Measurement of activation cross-section of long-lived products in deuteron induced nuclear reactions on palladium in the 30-50 MeV energy range

x4freetext: Measurement of activation cross-section of long-lived
products in deuteron induced nuclear reactions on
palladium in the 30-50 MeV energy range

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.128, p.297 (2017)

x4codes.hlp: Catholic Univ. of Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium

x4freetext: High purity, natural 0.008 mm Pd foils (Goodfellow)
were used interleaved with Al 0.05 mm monitor foils.
The irradiations
took place at a constant beam current 32 nA for 1 h
at LLN.
The incident beam energies were 50 MeV.
The radioactivity of each sample and
monitor foil was measured nondestructively by HPGe
spectrometry four times.
The decay data were taken from NUDAT.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Nuclear Data Services (Doc. series of NDS), No.1211 (2001)

x4freetext: Chapter 4
The uncertainty of the energy of the
bombarding beam in the middle of each irradiated foil
was estimated combining the uncertainties of the
energy degradation depending on the thickness of the
target foils in the stack and the energy straggling.
The uncertainties of the cross-section
values were estimated in the standard way: the
independent relative errors of the linearly
contributing processes were summed quadratically and
the square root of the sum was taken. The average
uncertainty was found to be 10-20%.
number of target nuclei (3%);
detector efficiency (5%);
beam current(7%);
statistical and peak fitting (1-20%)
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields.
